The Gauteng Provincial Command Council will give an update on COVID-19 in Gauteng. The presentation will cover, The Comprehensive Health Response, Food Security & Social Relief, Social Mobilization & Human Solidarity, Law enforcement & Compliance. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng provincial government will host a briefing on Thursday. The Gauteng Provincial Command Council will give an update on COVID-19 in Gauteng. The province has the second highest coronavirus infections in the country. Gauteng accounts for 1,720 cases of the 7,808 national tally. READ: COVID-19: The worst is yet to come says Ramaphosa There has been 15 fatalities and 1,036 recoveries in South Africa’s most populous province. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.